{
  "texts": [
    "Resorting to human judgment provides one effective way to evaluate topic models, such as topic rating and word intrusion tasks (Lau et al 2014).",
    "Unfortunately, its reliance on human raters renders it expensive and time-consuming, limiting its feasibility for wide-scale comparisons.",
    "Owing to this, researchers generally depend on automatic evaluation metrics, such as the topic coherence and diversity mentioned in Sect. 2.2.",
    "However, these automatic metrics encounter the following two problems:",
    "• Inconsistent usage and settings of automatic metrics."
  ]
}